description._content: Description: Upper Vaulting over Northernmost Bay of Transept, showing cracks between cross-vaults and inner side of northern wall of Transept. Cracks indicated by arrows. Location: Jerusalem, Palestine Date: 17 August 1932 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/738 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
